    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using Neovim 0.11.0 in two split panes (Neovim takes up approx. half the columns or rows on the screen), after the other pane is closed, the Neovim window does not resize correcly and leaves the Neovim window in a mangled state with characters out of order. \n\nOn Neovim 0.10.4 this issue does not exist.\n\nVersion v0.11.0:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6ac4e308-5973-491b-a369-ea9f6339329b\n\nVersion v0.10.4:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/305e98b4-15ae-41c0-bcb5-e6f9e8ebf135\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* `nvim --clean`\n*  open a split pane on iTerm2 3.5.11\n*  close the split pane\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim window should resize to fill the remaining columns/rows available. Neovim window should look the same as if no split pane had been opened (the v0.10.4 behavior)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo. Vim 9.1.754\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
